[{"id":"FT582883","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"Which of the following is the optimal quantity of pollution to eliminate?","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p><img alt=\"The figure shows a table with 2 columns and 6 rows of data. The first column is labeled Quantity of Pollution Reduction (in tons), and the second column is labeled Total Benefit (in dollars). Row 1; Quantity of Pollution Reduction, 0, Total Benefit, 0. Row 2; Quantity of Pollution Reduction, 1, Total Benefit, $300. Row 3; Quantity of Pollution Reduction, 2, Total Benefit, $550. Row 4; Quantity of Pollution Reduction, 3, Total Benefit, $650. Row 5; Quantity of Pollution Reduction, 4, Total Benefit, $725. Row 6; Quantity of Pollution Reduction, 5, Total Benefit, $775.\" height=\"271\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/b0e34b1030e2b9d439dffa3326ec6621/original.png\" width=\"352\" /></p>\n\n<p>The table above shows the total benefit associated with reducing different levels of pollution on a small island. The cost of eliminating one ton of pollution is $150.</p>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p>5 tons</p>","<p>4 tons</p>","<p>3 tons</p>","<p>2 tons</p>","<p>1 tons</p>"],"answer":2}]